{
  "texts": [
    "With the employment of GA and NBC, for instance, the 6G-SQC project's success probability increased from an initial 45.17 to 98.68% upon project maturity, concurrently reducing costs from 0.499 to 0.411%.",
    "Similarly, utilizing GA alongside LR, the success probability rose from 56.42 to 99.29%, with costs decreasing from 0.492 to 0.418% after 100 iterations.",
    "Furthermore, we ranked the variables related to 6G-SQC projects using GA, NBC, and LR.",
    "The findings demonstrated a strong positive correlation between both analyses, thus supplying practitioners with a prioritization guide for impactful variables and formulating strategies based on their influence on project success.",
    "Significant variables such as Education and Training, Data Privacy, Quantum Computing Resources, Integration with Existing Networks, Error Detection and Correction, and Network Management were highlighted."
  ]
}